<div><ul><li><b>Two different memories</b>&nbsp;can have different characteristics - instructions may be held in&nbsp;<b>read-only memory</b>&nbsp;while data requires&nbsp;<b>read-write memory</b>.<br></li><li>There is&nbsp;<b>much more instruction memory</b>&nbsp;than data memory, so the instruction address and data bus are wider than the data address and data bus.</li></ul></div>